# Insights

## Source of truth

- **Product direction (canonical):** `docs/Analytics_Overhaul_Proposal.md` — PG-first query builder, Saved Insights, lock grammar
- Grain / fact contract: `docs/Database_Outline.md`
- Living board: `docs/Status.md`
- Implementation: `src/lib/insights.ts`, `src/screens/insights/`

## Insights is a hub (Jul 22 reframe)

Insights tab = a **card hub** (like Library / Create) with two tools:

- **Dashboard** (`InsightsDashboardScreen`) — the PG-first per-PG facet readout. A **fast, unsaved** look. **No saving here.**
- **Query builder** (`InsightsQueryBuilderScreen`, placeholder) — the real bet: a **nested, savable, lockable** query form (see below).

Routing: `InsightsStack` in `HomeScreen.tsx` (hub / dashboard / queryBuilder).

## Direction (locked)

- **Subject first:** Primary Group(s) required
- **Facets:** shape-driven atomic fields (reps / time / distance / load / set count) — show what was logged; never sum unlike units
- **Scope:** nest labels + set type = query-global WHERE; **variations / tools = per-PG** (soft, never enforced). Not rival lenses
- **Multi-PG:** one editable card per selected PG (Dashboard)
- **Category:** PG metadata for balance **saved views**, not home-screen lens
- **Read source:** `v_log_set_facts`; credit-each under the hood; complete logs only

## Shipped

- **Dashboard** = Phase 2 draft form + Phase 3a per-PG scope cards (variations/tools scoped per PG, soft `suggestedIds`). Load facet = avg when present (not tonnage). No persistence / lock.
- **Insights hub** (card select) + Dashboard / Query builder placeholder.

## Query builder direction (in progress — capability first)

Mirror the log/template builder family: **nested collapsing dropdowns** per layer; **lock per layer** → grammar-condensed line (expand to edit); **preview modal** for the expanded locked outline; **save/list/rename/delete** reusable asks (`saved_insights` — **ask before migrating**); reopen → dropdown=OPEN + lock=TRUE clean view, re-run live; per-exercise-query breakdown (modifiers / loads / variations) + totals line. Details in proposal §5–6 / §9 Phase 3.

